sec.p:
Peak calling was performed for MSL proteins from flyes of ♂M1[wt] and ♀ M1[wt]+MSL2 lines, as described previously (Sabirov et al., 2021). Briefly:


duplicates were removed with Picard (http://broadinstitute.github.io/picard/);

blacklist filtration was performed;

peak calling was performed using MACS version 2 against nonspecific IgG (Zhang et al., 2008), with a soft p-value threshold of 1 × 10−2 for further irreproducible discovery rate (IDR) analysis.

Reproducibility was assessed using the IDR pipeline, with p-value thresholds of 0.05 for true replicates and 0.01 for pseudoreplicates. All samples showed ideal reproducibility [both the rescue ratio (RR) and self-consistency ratio (SR) were less than 2; thus, an “optimal” set of highly-reproduced peaks was chosen for each sample.
